\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16122257 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 Well let me see. Oh I was married then. Yes and my husband was working for him \'85 \'85 a long long time ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13721485 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 \'85 \'85 During the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16122257 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 After that, 1948 \'85 yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13721485 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 What had your mother done before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16122257 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 
Well Mother used to be with her grandmother, used to work for her, you see, used to be like I did, help in the house, you see, but she had another lady come in, one used to do the washing for her, and
 another one used to come and do the odds and ends at times, you know, and of course she was pretty well off you see. Oh yes. I wouldn't mind that life over again but not with the - not with having rheumatic }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2179837\charrsid9002493 fever.?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493  
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13721485 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 There was too much sickness wasn't there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16122257 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13721485 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 An awful lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16122257 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 Afterwards I got fine. (BANGING) Beautiful I was till I got married and all my troubles started. (BANGING)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13721485 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 Were your parents strict
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16122257 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 Oh yes we had to be in by ten, not to play outside, we played out of course top of the street \'85 \'85
 then we used to go up the park on a Sunday. Who you going with, yes, who you going with, you know she'd be very funny. Getting into mischief, all that
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13721485 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16122257 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493  \'85\'85\'85\'85.. in those days you walked round the bandstand, you
 know, the boys and girls and give one another eyes you know, a bit of fun that's all, like everything. Different today, but still.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13721485 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 Had you any spending money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16122257 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 Well Dad used to treat me and used to go to theatres, and if I wanted any money I co
uld have it, clothe me, I had everything I wanted, plenty of good food and everything, you see, so I was very lucky. Very lucky. (TOGETHER) Beg pardon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13721485 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 Had you any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16122257 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 Any fence? Money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13721485 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 Pets, cats, dogs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16122257 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 Pets, yes. Oh, pets, don't t
alk about pets. I had my Minnie as I call her, it was a he really. When mother was alive we all went down one Christmas I think it was to Gran, we used to go down there you see, now and again -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13721485 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 Where did she live?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16122257 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 Gravesend, and Minnie of course
 she would be with my grandmother but she didn't no work - she had a servant then and she looked after her, she was her sister you see. Of course mother, mother's mother died when she was 12 and she used to look after her, Dad and that and the sister and 
b
rother and then Grannie said oh well I'll take Minnie and Ted, she said - of course she educated him, and Mother's on her own you see, and she went to - Grannies before - yes went to Gran's afterwards that's right, of course she got on, they got married y
ou see so - and then she used to be East Dulwich you see when she started working for her Granny that's right, just down the other end you know, through the Oval way, Oval - no The Oval, wasn't it, Kennington way, through that way I know to Dulwich.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13721485 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 Kennington.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16122257 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 Yes, that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13721485 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 How about holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16122257 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 Well we used to have a holiday, we used to go to Yarmouth and Ramsgate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13721485 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 How long for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16122257 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 Oh a week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13721485 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 All of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16122257 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 Not all the lot of us. Dad couldn't always go you see because 
of the business of course there wouldn't be all of us there, there'd he about - Arthur, Gilbey, my sister, and Grace perhaps, sometimes she went back to Granny or something. I know once we all was there, all down there, there was us seven children, mother
 and father and the friend we used to have, some lodger we had in those days when we were down Crowndale Road. 10 of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13721485 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 \'85.Quite a lot
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16122257 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 Yes. Oh we used to have a lovely time, loved riding on the donkeys. We used to play football when we were down 
there, no rounders with the ball, we used to be all spread round and have a game rounders, it was lovely. And when I was a child I know when my mother went down there when I was little, we went to Ramsgate and there used to be little goat carts in those d
ays and you know the nanny goat was in the front, used to drive them, it used to be - it used to be lovely. They all went you see afterwards. They were lovely days, you know, those days, the good old days. And so cheap everything was then, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13721485 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 Were your parents churchgoers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16122257 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 Chapel. The Mission}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16649685\charrsid9002493  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 Chapel and we was christened I think in a chapel, at Wolfendale, down in Somers Town, the Rev (INT. SPEAKING ALSO) Yes, yes, and he was a lovely man. I had him afterwards when I got married, he lived to
 a good age and it was ever so nice. It puts me in mind of this gentleman the Reverend Joyce over in the Isle of Wight. He's a lovely speaker, I don't know if you've ever heard him first thing in the morning just before the news comes on., oh he does give
 
a lovely - oh he's lovely to hear, he's beautiful. And I always remember when I was at the hospital, taken bad after I come home from Canada, I met with an accident you see the third time, the second time, and he came and saw me in Hospital and I thought 
w
hat a nice gentleman he was, and he told me about one of our men who used to be at Hesketh House, how he used to send eggs to different people who was ill, he used to have a chicken farm and wonderful, you know. Oh he was lovely that man, he never preache
d about anything about God or anything like that, \'85 \'85
 Do your work, you know, he was just nice. And another one over at Holy Trinity Church over there in Albany Street, Father Rose, he was another nice man, don't matter where you was, anywhere, he'd acknowl
edge you, come across, ask how you were. Mother used to like him.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13721485 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 So (BELL RINGS)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16122257 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 \'85 you see that's the shop, oil shop there, it's still there but not, it's all modern you see now and so that's -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13721485 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 Your bedroom at the top and whose bedroom is that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16122257 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 
That was the big bedroom. Now I used to look out that window we used to get to the window because we had to be careful, oh we had to be in bed at ten Dad wouldn't \'85 never used to answer the door no more after ten, used to be very funny like th
at, and I used to look out that window and he'd call up \'85 \'85
 looking out that window, you know, and we used to watch the children over the park because market place on the corner and then in front of there was a stall, fish stall, and then on each side was 
these shops, and afterwards and they didn't used to shut till 12}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9002493  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 you know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13721485 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1787301\charrsid9002493 \'85
